# Shell scripts run on Linux (WSL/EC2/CI) — force LF regardless of the checkout OS. Found
# 2026-07-02: no .gitattributes existed, so a Windows working tree could silently accumulate CRLF
# (git blob stayed clean LF, only the local disk copy was corrupted) — `sh deploy/aws-ec2-test/
# backup.sh` failed with "illegal option -" under WSL until the local files were reset from HEAD.
# This doesn't fix a past commit (there was none to fix), it stops it from ever becoming one.
*.sh text eol=lf
